parameters.text:
=Write a personalized first line for a cold email to this prospect:
Recipient Details:

Name: {{ $('Process CSV Upload').first().json['First Name'] }} {{ $('Process CSV Upload').first().json['Last Name'] }}
Company: {{ $('Process CSV Upload').first().json.Company }}

Research Insights:

Pain Points: {{ $json.pain_points }}
Business Priorities: {{ $json.business_priorities }}
Conversation Starters: {{ $json.conversation_starters }}
Likely Objections: {{ $json.likely_objections }}
Best Timing Context: {{ $json.best_timing }}
Personalization Angle: {{ $json.personalization_angle }}
Industry Insights: {{ $json.industry_insights }}

My Services:
Product/service: {{ $('Campaign Request Form').first().json['Your Product/Service'] }}
Value Proposition: {{ $('Campaign Request Form').first().json['Value Proposition'] }}

Based on these insights, create a first line that:

Demonstrates understanding of their specific situation
References something timely or relevant to them right now
Subtly hints at why you're reaching out without being pushy
Is friendly and personalized
Feels like it was written specifically for them, not mass-produced

Example first lines:
"I noticed you recently spoke at TechCon about sustainable AI infrastructure—your point about reducing computational waste by 40% really challenged how I think about model optimization."

"Your LinkedIn post about the challenges of scaling a remote team from 10 to 100 people resonated with me, especially since we just hit similar growing pains at [Your Company]."

"Congratulations on the Series B! I saw TechCrunch mentioned you're planning to expand into the European market—that's exactly the journey we helped [Similar Company] navigate last year."

"I've been following [Their Company]'s journey since your pivot from B2C to B2B last quarter, and your approach to repositioning the brand without losing core users was impressive."

"Just listened to your interview on the Marketing Masters podcast where you mentioned struggling to find good attribution models for PLG companies—we actually just cracked this problem for a similar SaaS."

Write only the personalized first line, nothing else. Do not mention the prospect's name.
